âœ”ï¸ Tip:

Watch your baby closely during feeds. If theyâ€™re gulping, sputtering, or falling asleep mid-feed, it might be time to adjust the flow rate.

4. ğŸƒ Take Breaks and Burp Often

Donâ€™t wait until the end of the bottle to burp your baby. Frequent pauses allow trapped air to escape before it builds up.

